\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 #107d A Sticky Problem \

\b0 1 Then there were two [other] people, once upon a time, named Q\uc0\u596 \u768 -n\u603 \u769  and Q\u596 \u768 -\u331 \u596 \u769 . [1]\
2 One morning they were going along together, when [one of them] said: \
3 "Let's go parakeet-trapping early tomorrow morning, okay?"\
 4 So the next morning they went off together. \
5 When they had finished laying the parakeet-traps, a parakeet came and got stuck [2 ] on it--on [the trap] of Q\uc0\u596 \u768 -n\u603 \u769 .\
6 Thereupon Q\uc0\u596 \u768 -\u331 \u596 \u769  [the YL] said, "Friend, it's stuck [3] on yours!"\
7 Then, another one got stuck over on [the trap] of Q\uc0\u596 \u768 -\u331 \u596 \u769  [the BL].\
8 At this, he [4] said, "Friend, there's one stuck [5] on yours too!"\
9 Then the two of them got furious at each other [6] and began fighting. [7] \
10 As they fought, they ended up down in the river--and [all because] he [the YL]  had said "The parakeets aren't paying any attention to yours!" [8]\
\

